	<conbody>
		<section id="navigation_title_term">
			<p>
				<b>Definition</b>
			</p>
			<p>An alternative title for a topic, specified as an attribute on a topicref element.</p>
			<p>
				<b>Usage</b>
			</p>
			<p>Navigation titles are usually shorter than the full title, or they could be set, as in the following example, to allow the use of 'scope="peer"' in related links (see <xref href="related_links_element.dita" scope="peer">Related links</xref>).</p>
			<p>
				<b>Example</b>
			</p>
			<p>
			<codeblock>
&lt;concept id="audience"&gt;
&lt;title&gt;Audience&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;titlealts&gt;&lt;navtitle&gt;Audience&lt;/navtitle&gt;&lt;/titlealts&gt;
&lt;shortdesc/&gt;
&lt;prolog&gt;			
			</codeblock>
			</p>
		</section>
	</conbody>
</concept>
